Package uk.gov.gchq.gaffer.parquetstore.operation.addelements.impl

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AggregateAndSortTempData
    Creates parallel tasks aggregate and sort the unsorted data for a given group and indexed column.
    AggregateGafferRowsFunction
    This is used by the Spark reduceByKey method to aggregate two GenericRowWithSchema's using the Gaffer aggregator's.
    AggregateGroupSplit
    Aggregates and sorts a directory of parquet files that represents a single group so each group can be processed in parallel.
    CalculateSplitPointsFromIndex
    Generates the split points from the GraphIndex and uses the min values per file as the split points
    CalculateSplitPointsFromIterable
    Generates the split points from an Iterable of Elements by selecting a sample of the data, sorting that sample and then pulling out the relevant objects to act as the split points
    ExtractKeyFromRow
    This class is used to extract the key from each Row using the set of groupBy column names.
    GenerateIndexForColumnGroup
    Generates the index for a single group directory.
    GenerateIndices
    Generates and processes the tasks (GenerateIndexForColumnGroup) that will generate the index for each sorted directories data.
    SortFullGroup
    This class is used to sort the data for a single group by loading in the /aggregate folder within a group
    SortGroupSplit
    This class is used to sort the data for a single split of a group by loading in the /aggregate/split folder within a group
    WriteUnsortedData
    Takes an Iterator of Element's and writes the elements out into Parquet files split into directories for each group.
